##A barber with 30,000 medical staff in Wuhan

DICTATION: Johnny

Interview, by Yang Xi

Our goal and intention is to preserve the beauty of our staff as much as possible in a safe environment. 1

I am a hair stylist in Wuhan, today (March 12)8:30 am, I drive pick up two partners, an hour later arrived in Hebei Han medical team in the hotel. This is the third time we've been to this hotel.

River bank shelter hospital after the cabin, Hebei Medical Team in the hotel on-site standby rest. A lot of medical staff before cut hair feel not good, want to trim again, some are not cut before, the hair is very long, asked us to come.

When I got there, a lot of people's hair was all messed up. Did I say you cut your own hair? Some said it was cut by the department nurse, some said it was cut by the department doctor. They couldn't find a barber, so they cut each other's hair, cut each other's hair with surgical scissors, or borrow a razor from a hotel.

The three of us spent the morning trimming over 30 people. In the afternoon, I went to another hotel, where the rest of the Hebei medical team and the Anhui Medical Team stayed, cutting more than 70 people until about 7 o'clock in the evening.

A day of hair cut, I did not count, let alone more than 10 Jins, piled up about half as much as a large garbage can.

I joined the volunteer team on Feb. 15, and I was particularly impressed. It was snowing, the city was gray, empty, and desolate, just like the scene in the movie wandering Earth.

We received the Han medical team in the early days because they were relatively safe at that time. During that week, nearly 1,000 or 2,000 medical teams came to Wuhan every day. I remember very clearly that the first day they served the Hainan medical team and the Shaanxi medical team. The total number of medical staff was about 200, we had seven or eight barbers cutting from after eight in the morning until half past one in the morning. Because a lot of people are going to be in the Bright Valley Shelter Hospital in the early hours of the morning, so we have to get their hair done before then.

Hairdressers also wear protective clothing, face masks and gloves. I wasn't used to it at first, and I suggested that we don't need to wear protective clothing, that these things should be left to the medical staff, who need them more. But the volunteers in charge of coordination said that the medical team came in healthy, but we can not guarantee the condition of the volunteers on site, so wearing protective clothing is to protect both ourselves and them. So I took it. In fact, I was just distressed, because at that time the supplies were not particularly sufficient, well, we are all at home more than 20 days of isolation, I think since everyone is healthy, it is not necessary to wear protective clothing.

When you cut your hair with gloves on, you often cut your gloves because you don't know the feel and you can't even catch the hair. So for a while in the beginning, we cut our hair not to look good, but to help them solve their problems, shave it off, shorten it, thin it, make it easier for them to wash, dry it, and not get infected. Usually we cut a hair to take half an hour, an hour, this time really is 5 to 10 minutes a person, the most exaggerated day I cut about 80 people.

I used to get six or eight customers a day, ten at the most, and I felt very busy. But that day down, although also feel a little tired, but not usually that kind of feeling of fatigue. I guess I had a little bit of a stress reaction, you know, excitement, like I was doing something noble.

2

The decision to do this has to do with a neighbor of mine.

On February 13, she called me to ask if I was in Wuhan and if I could give her a haircut. She's a nurse in the facial features department at Children's Hospital, on a mission to mount thor. She was a little choked up on the phone.

We used to be neighbors, and, coincidentally, she'd come in from work, and I'd come in from work, and she'd come in from work, and most of the time, she'd just bump into each other in the stairwell, boom. She's been spending a lot of time with my wife, and her son is about my son's age, and we've been hanging out.

When she called me on this phone, she said she was afraid to go home and cut it so her son wouldn't see it. She was afraid to let me go to the hospital, too, for fear that it would be bad for me. Then her husband picked me up and went to her mother's house to get it cut. On the way, her husband said that she did cry when she was given the assignment, because of fear. Plus, if you cut your hair short, girls will still miss it.

After we met, I asked her how to cut her hair. She asked if she could get a girl's crew cut? I was shocked, I said female crew cut, never heard of the word, why to cut crew cut? She said it was dangerous for us to go there, and that we didn't know what it would be like to go there, and in order to avoid infection, there had to be no hair sticking out where the cap was, and we had to shave off both sides. So she came up with a crew cut.

At that time, I feel very uncomfortable, a very beautiful girl suddenly said to cut crew-cut, the feeling you have no way to understand. Her original hair style is more fashionable in the long hair, Perm. I just thought I'd make her as pretty as I could, and I suggested she just shave off the sides and keep the top ones.

What kind of hairstyle did she say it was? I said, have you seen G.E.M.'s hair? Both sides down, one on top. It's very handsome, too. I combed her hair, and there was a braid up there. Her hair is very much, very hard, not very good tie, I tied a long time, the lower part of the fear of infection shaved, and cut the length of the upper layer to the shoulders, so that she can later braid. After cutting, she looked at herself in the mirror and thought it was OK.

Later, the hairstyle became the most cared for hairstyle by women in the first line after baldness. In fact, shaved head but not enough friction, masks, hats wear, easy to run. On the contrary, the hairstyle both reduced the risk of infection and made it easier to wash. They had to wash their hair every day and didn't have enough rest time so that they could wash it quickly and get some rest. They'll be prettier when the epidemic's over.

Before that, I also saw the video of the paramedics shaving their heads and crying on it, and it didn't touch me that much. But when it happened to someone I knew, it hit me so hard that I said I had to do it.

I got a call from her on February 13 to cut her hair, and I didn't go out the next day for Valentine's Day. At that time also was thinking, go out to have to take a big risk, the home still has the child, a little can not make up one's mind. My wife used to be a nurse, and she was really understanding, and then we talked, and she said, "go ahead. ".

3

In the beginning, many girls cut and cried. To tell the truth, I am a more sensitive person, see these scenes often can not help.

I was particularly impressed by a girl from the Foshan medical team, whose hair was thigh-length. She is a Hanfu Fan, the home has dozens of Hanfu, usually love the United States, like the hair into a variety of retro modeling, wearing Hanfu to go out for photographs. That day cut hair, she said the first knife must be her own cut, otherwise reluctant to part.

She didn't say how long it had been there, but I was able to make a preliminary estimate that it was at least 10 years old. When she cut the knife, she literally said it felt like cutting herself in a movie, tears streaming down her face, and she was shaking.

After she cut it, I comforted her. I said I didn't have to cut it so clean. I kept her hair as long as I could, shaved off the inside, and cut the outer layer below the breast. When she was done, she smiled and said she thought it looked good. And I thought, as a hairdresser, it was really fulfilling to be able to help them with this.

I've also met some pretty young girls who have had big waves and curls and dyed their hair before, joking that it was made 680 years ago, and you'll lose it. It's a very expensive haircut. They were like this to make fun of, feel that they are also very helpless.

We went there because we wanted to preserve their beauty, their femininity, as much as possible, in a safe environment. But a lot of girls start off by saying, "shave off the sides and the back. ". She said I could come back alive, and look as pretty as I wanted, and my hair could grow back if I cut it short, but if I went in and I didn't come out, there was only one life, and I couldn't risk it.

Once I gave a Guangxi medical team of a girl cut hair, I thought, anyway, stay a round inch is better. I talked to her, and when I was done, she said no, shave it off. I asked her why, and she said I shaved it off in the hope that I would be healthy enough to go back and see my children.

The male nurse is also like this, begin to say I do not ask you to cut what hairstyle, short line. Basically, it's mostly shaved round inches, a little longer than a shaved head, three millimeters. Or you can just push the light. And then the periphery is almost all shaved, cut to about 1 cm above, play very thin, called Mao inch, just a few of these models.

Because we are not early contact into the ward's medical staff, they do not understand the virus, in fact, we will start a little bit of panic. But later this period of time, from the ward out of the medical care we also meet, they said that I can give a better cut, give me a haircut? Maybe once they're inside, they'll get to know the virus better, lose their fear. A lot of people called me in the middle of the day and said they wanted to have their hair cut again, so I went back and helped them redesign it and trim it. They say they see hope, and it may not be long before they can go home.

4

We haven't had a break since February 15th. In fact, there's no service at all. The medical team supporting Wuhan has about 30,000 people. Our team has served less than 10,000 people. Several volunteer teams are also doing this.

Every day from 11:30 to 12:00 noon, we and the medical staff together to pick up a box of food, we go to eat in groups. The boxed meals vary from place to place, and the Han medical team is said to be offering a standard of 200 yuan per person per day, or 100 yuan per meal. I feel like there are good things and there are bad things. I've been to one of the medical team's hotels before, and the hotel kitchen happens to have no breaks. It's a buffet. It's pretty good. It's got meat and shrimp, and it's got after-dinner fruit. It's definitely up to $200 a day. There are places that can not be reached, but in the later stages, the medical team's supplies are basically guaranteed.

Most of them come for haircuts, probably in their "hand-washing" clothes, some in their own clothes, some in disposable scrubs or isolation suits. They're careful, they're worried about what it's GonNa do to us, and a lot of people are nervous, too, and they're gonNA take their hand sanitizer, and they're gonNA spray it on us. Sometimes spray too much, the top of the cloth will be a bit wet, when the encirclement will be a bit cold.

Tools are one guest one disinfection, at the end of each day, we will also use all the alcohol spray again, as well as do maintenance. A week ago, my electric pusher broke down. Happens to be a volunteer team inside a boss, he is specialized in doing hairdressing tools, the shop inside the tools out to us for free use.

Too much alcohol, too dry hands, the skin will wrinkle, will be dark, not shiny, gray, like the old wrinkled hands. Later, the team leader in charge of coordination also gave each of us hand cream. When the medics had more supplies, they saw how hard we were working, and they gave us their own alcohol Gel, which was much better than spraying alcohol directly.

In addition to the early just come to the medical team, behind our services, more than 99% of the medical care is not washed hair. Perhaps they had just come out of the cabin, back to the hotel, was very tired of a state, as soon as you see a haircut, hurry to line up. A lot of people have their hair tied up, or flattened and greasy by a hat. We will look at the degree of hair deformation, if it is very influential haircut, such as hair is bent, hair roots are inverted, you must spray water and then cut.

The venue facilities for hairdressing, in a word, is all simple, what there is on the spot with what. Some places are just a plastic stool, others may be a chair with a backrest. There are no mirrors, and many people habitually turn their phones on after a haircut, either with a camera or by simply shining a light on the glass of the phone's screen.

We talk to them when we're not too busy. For example, when do you think it will be unsealed? How long will it take.

In just over a month, the change in care has been noticeable. Before entering the cabin, most people are quite nervous, do not know what will face. Some of the young doctors were excited and eager to try. Slowly, as more patients leave the hospital and fewer are diagnosed or suspected, many doctors discuss the condition during haircuts, such as which bed the patient is in. Recently, I hear more and more that they are homesick and talking about their children. Many people also make video calls to their families during haircuts to show their babies that their mothers got a haircut today and that volunteer uncles had come to give their mothers a haircut.

5

I've been living apart from my family since I started doing this. I now live in a friend rent house, he went out of town did not come back, give me the key, said you usually just to help me take care of it. Every night when I go back to my place, I spray myself full of alcohol when I walk in the door, including the soles of my shoes, and then I hang my clothes on the balcony, which is basically the same outfit that comes and goes.

We also have a small partner, straight to sleep in the car, two cut late, just inside the hotel has a spare room, to help arrange the hotel stay.

I am Hubei Xiantao people, to Wuhan for 20 years, just settled in Wuhan last year. In 2000, when I was 18, I wanted to learn a trade because I didn't study. Coincidentally, the day I came to Wuhan was also February 14.

I've owned a lot of barbershops in my time, but they're not very well run, and sometimes it can be a matter of opportunity. In the past few years or good, but also accumulated a certain network, with a lot of students. Around 2014,2015, I wanted to do a bit more high-end store, and together with two friends invested about 1.8 million. But at that time Wuhan was not very receptive to this type of store, a loss of one hundred thousand, the front of all the savings have been lost, still owe a little debt. Then I came out to work for two years, and now a friend co-opened a small studio, more than 50 flat, five chairs, two shampoo bed.

On December 31 last year, I did a client's hair, and it was about 1:00 a.m. on January 1 when I finished work. He showed me a screenshot from a friend of his saying there was pneumonia in the south China seafood market. And I said, "what is this? "? He said his friend worked at the hospital, said it was SARS. But we didn't care, and the next day it was business as usual.

There were so many guests that we worked day and night. On January 18, around the New Year's Eve, there were still a lot of guests, but one after another began to see people wearing masks. Some customers warned us to pay attention, I asked the technician to buy masks, they said the surrounding pharmacies sold out of masks, I immediately felt the situation is serious. I remember going to a dozen pharmacies and buying three packs of generic surgical masks, which were no longer available on the N95, so we wore double-decker surgical masks.

Years ago we were open until the 12th month of the Twelfth Lunar Month (January 23) , the day of the city's closure. Because there are some clients to do their hair, so I thought I would help them as much as possible, and then go back home.

January 23rd. When I got up, it was after 10:00. The city was closed. I sent a quick message to the guests to cancel the appointment, but they couldn't get through to me. I just closed the store, called my parents and said I couldn't go back, and they especially understood, because our hometown is also quite strict, Wuhan closed on the 23rd, Xiantao closed on the 24th, we all stay at home, every day a video call to report a safe.

I wonder if it is possible to resume work at the end of April or the beginning of May. This period of time, all Wuhan people have not cut their hair, as long as the opening, the first time the barber shop is certainly the busiest. But the difficulty of returning to work in the early stage is relatively big, it is impossible to allow such a large area of personnel to gather at once, and many people will still worry that public places are better not to go.

I do not worry after the resumption of work will have a special big impact, are old customers, normal income or will come in. And the studio rent pressure is relatively small. Chains may struggle to survive, rents are high, most are itinerant, and they are under pressure to pay staff. They rely on cash flow, once the funding chain is broken, it is difficult to survive.

6

I had no income for two months, and I had to pay about 8,000 a month in mortgage and car payments, plus rent for the store. So far, the landlord hasn't made it clear that he wants to reduce the rent. To be honest, I'm stuck with a credit card for a while.

Fortunately, there are a lot of children's online classes are free, let me relax a little bit. My Son is 6 years old this year, will soon start the first grade, enrolled in a lot of small convergence Pei you class, language, mathematics, English, including piano, painting these have learned. I don't think I'M GONNA make it two months if I have to pay to go back to these enrichment classes.

I am Moonlight clan, earned money to pay the mortgage, car loans, plus the child's education fees, basically no. In the past, when I had savings, I always thought of men, AH, must do business, thinking to open a shop, to invest, to expand the business, always feel money is waiting for us to make like. Now I know one thing, a man must have savings. I usually may have to save a little bit more, save money, can be prepared for a rainy day.

A lot of people said, then why don't you go for a haircut? I said people are fighting with their lives. How can we be embarrassed? We really didn't think of collecting money when we did this thing. A friend asked, why take the risk? I joked that there is a saying, "when the country is in crisis, every man has his responsibility. " All medical teams from all over the country have come to support Wuhan. They have already reached the first-level combat readiness. At this time, we can take our scissors and stand on the front line with the medical staff, is to give them a push.

When I first started out as a volunteer, I was careful not to open the door, never opened the window, went down to work and sprayed the door handle with alcohol on the way back. Next thing I know, there's a bunch of volunteers on the road. Wuhan is so big, so densely populated, and it takes so many people to do so much for these people, to serve the community, to buy groceries, to run errands... especially the delivery guys, who are still the same, riding an electric bike down the street is a real sweat on their hands. We have a few young people in the volunteer team, 90, they joked that they are now the streets of the most beautiful boy.

Today, a paramedic asked me if the Cherry blossoms were in bloom? I said that at this time of year, the Liberation Park, the riverbank and the Qingchuan pavilion in Wuhan, as well as the Cherry Gardens in Wuhan and East L. , can be seen. Is She far? Can we go? They're cute. They said I just wanted to check it out, so if I don't get out of the car, can I just check it out in the car?

At that time, I thought, in fact, for these medical personnel on standby, whether the government could consider getting a tour bus, carrying them, let them see Wuhan, understand Wuhan. They have come all this way and paid so much. Up to now, we still don't know what Wuhan is like. In their impression, Wuhan is from the hotel to the ward, from the ward to the hotel. Some people say, I do not know the weather outside, do not know the time outside, do not know now outside is the star or The Sun.

But they couldn't get out because their orders were to stay in the hotel. Now it is mid-march, Cherry blossom is like this, may be to early April, Qingming Festival when there is no.
